President Obama has announced that Jeffrey Zients, the current Deputy Director for Management and Chief Performance Officer, will serve as the Acting Director of the Office of Management and Budget. Zients has been confirmed by the Senate in 2009 and has extensive business experience as a CEO, management consultant, and entrepreneur. He has served as CEO and Chairman of The Advisory Board Company and Chairman of the Corporate Executive Board. Zients also co-founded The Urban Alliance Foundation, a non-profit organization that provides economically disadvantaged youth with paid internships and job training. He graduated summa cum laude from Duke University and resides in Washington, D.C. with his wife and four children.